19/01/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Thousands of tobacco growers gathered on Tuesday (January 18th) in front of parliament to protest the purchase price of their crops. 
The situation got tense when protestors started hurling stones and bottles at police and tried to breach a cordon and enter the building. 
Some windows ended up being smashed.
Inside, lawmakers from the ruling coalition and the opposition SDSM were heatedly debating the situation in the sector. 
Tobacco growers staged a protest in front of the headquarters of the SDSM as well, asking the party not to use the situation for political gain. 
(MIA, A1, Kanal 5 - 18/01/11)
